caption: My favorite iced mocha exists here. Rosemary breakfast sandwiches and breakfast burritos are very yummy. I come here every time I’m in Park Slope.
Ordered an LGBT with Turkey on gluten free bread. Received an LGBT 9with Canadian bacon), no turkey and on regular whole grain bread. Disappointed as I've enjoyed this cafe over the years.
The best biscuit breakfast sandwich in all the land. Awesome burritos, great coffee.
Horrible boss. Call you and leave messages and email you on your day off and after work to let you know you forgot to take out a garbage bag. The most heinous micro manager I've ever worked for.
One of the best highlights of Park Slope. Good food, great staff. Love Naidre's.
Breakfast burriyosy!
The food is phenomenal!
Best tofu scramble ever! Coffee is yummy, too. They often serve vegan cookies as well. Coffee is delish. Staff is welcoming and kind; service is excellent. Small place & no restrooms.
Awesome biscuit egg sandwiches!!!

I really do like it here. They make a wonderful vegan breakfast scramble plate. I get it every time and it’s always delicious. The vegan chocolate chip cookie is also amazing. The one guy who works here really treated me and my boyfriend very well, so I was appreciating the LGBT kindness for sure. Limited seating and there’s not a lot of ambience. But it’s great for just easy and quick breakfast.
They always serve quality food: breakfast, lunch or dinner. There's always a nice spot to sit and the staff are really chill and nice.

great food. goos vegetarian/vegan options. excellent service
(Translated by Google) Great, the muffins are extra  (Original) Super, les muffins sont extra

Had a great BLT sandwich on sourdough. You could really tell the tomatoes and lettuce were very fresh! Staff was kind and friendly. Would recommend to anyone in the area.
Best biscuits ever

My ex-girlfriend introduced me to this place and I still love it. A friend from my neighborhood actually works there which was surprising. She's the one who's cooking the food so I got to give her credit and be biased at the same time. Lol.
Excellent pizza and refreshments, great service, and Piero was awesome!

I wish they had more vegan items on their menu because their food is really high quality. I had the tofu scramble plate and the only reason I'm not giving it 5 stars is because besides the side salad seemed to overwhelm the actual tofu scramble, and the scramble itself was very oily (but delicious otherwise). I think you could pull back on the oil and it would still taste just as good and probably even better, maybe use some Kala Namak. Wish you guys had gluten free AND vegan bread.
Naidre's is always reliable for a quick and fresh bite to eat.  Their breakfast burrito is phenomenal as is their fresh turkey sandwich.

Perfect to pick up breakfast on the way to work. They have these jalapeño cheddar biscuits that are to DIE FOR... really good for a BEC. Nice little selection of out of the box desserts and pastries. The almond croissant is the best I’ve ever had.
We go here multiple times a week during our morning walk. Always great coffee and pastries!

I just love this little café on 7th Ave! My go to spot for delicious croissants and the most amazing soups, sandwiches, and wraps. Especially on these cold winter days! Not to mention their amazing staff, always so welcoming!! #comfortfood

A great cafe in the heart of Park Slope. The coffee and food is amazing. I highly recommend getting the breakfast sandwich on a bagel, but you can't go wrong with any of their options. For lunch I recommend their grilled cheese or burritos. They also have amazing pasteries as well. And if you are vegan they have pleanty of options as well.
Great friendly service. Solid food and coffee.
Fresh healthy food
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
Great coffee, staff and let's not forget their croissants!!!!
Man this place is a neighborhood staple. I remember when there was nothing on 7th Ave. I am glad to see them survive for so long. I bet it wasn't easy.
They have a wide variety of breakfast and lunch options.
Great service and food
Amazing biscuits and breakfast sandwiches!  No AMEX.

Amazing. Do your mouth a favor and get a biscuit breakfast sandwich from this delightful establishment. Your mouth will be happy, your stomach will be happy, and you will be happy!! Awesome staff, quick service, dank coffee, and a cool location. What are you waiting for? I know you're hungry. Pay them a visit! I can't wait to make a return trip.

A true staple cafe in Park Slope, always had fresh organic coffee before it was the trend. Amazing vegan options for food and the people who work there are so friendly. Happy we still have neighborhood cafes like this when there are so many commercial spots trying to do the same thing as Naidre’s. TIP- try the vegan chocolate chip cookies they’re the best in south Brooklyn !
Great breakfast, warm spot on a cold morning.
Have been coming here for years, always great food and service. Lots of Vegan and gluten free options too. Also got one of the best birthday cakes I’ve ever had here. Soooo good.
Solid egg, avacado and cheese sandwich. Staff is quick and helpful. Gets you what you to start your day and be on your way!
Great place and opens early! Bring your electronics fully charged as no outlets to recharge.
Great coffee, homemade pastries;
Great neighborhood place. Amazing almond croissants. A bit pricey, but good quality food. One of my go to spots in Bklyn.
Lovely, casual place. Friendly staff. Reasonably priced vegan options and they take cards! Tip: the full food menu is on the paper menu next to the register, not on the chalkboard.
Try the jalapeno cheddar biscuits

Solid little cafe with good, hearty sandwiches and delicious fresh baked goods. They don't have a lot of seating, so it's more of a order and go kind of place but it's perfect if you're planning to hang out in Prospect Park and want to bring a picnic or some lunch.  Their breakfast sandwich on a fresh made biscuit is a must!
They have the ingredients available to look up for their food.
Classic breakfast features, sandwiches, etc. Very friendly staff. A good neighbourhood option.
Cute neighborhood place where everything is delicious- amazing pastries and desserts, vegan options, and a killer breakfast burrito
Love the vegan breakfast option.
Great coffee & food! This is a family-owned neighborhood place that has been here for many years for good reason! Also has really good Gluten-free products.
Favorite neighborhood spot. Good food, teas and coffees.  Great place to get a personalized cake for parties.

A friendly little neighborhood coffee shop with interesting cappuccinos and latte's. The staff is really nice and the service was fast. The prices are comparable to most coffee shops in the general area.

I basically live on their breakfast burritos. My current favorite is the El Presidente (eggs, rice, beans, cheddar, sour cream, guacamole). I ask them to add chorizo to it to give it a little more heft. The burrito is big enough that I can divide it over two meals.
Fantastic breakfast sandwiches and coffee. As others have noted, this is not a place where you can linger slowly over a cup of coffee, but I've never had even the slightest problem with the service.

I LOVE this bakery!  I cannot say enough nice things-- we've ordered my son's birthday cake from Naidre's every year since he was born-- their cakes are delicious and made with love.  The owner and baker, Janice, is the nicest person in the world to work with and very accommodating.  The prices are very reasonable considering the quality of the cake and the fact that they DELIVER-- On a SUNDAY no less!  Seriously-- I never write reviews-- but need everyone to know what a gem of a place this really is.

It's on the pricier side, but everything is homemade (except, I think, the bagels), with good vegetarian and vegan options, and super tasty to boot!  I agree with some of the comments below about the sometimes brusque service, but I'm there to get good food, not make friends or camp at a table forever (there are like 4 tables there, so I try to be considerate of others waiting to have their meal), so I guess it bothers me less.  This place would be a 4 for me (because of the lack of tables), but since they just started taking credit cards a couple weeks ago, I think that bumps it up to a 5.  (Try a sausage, egg, and cheese on a rosemary biscuit. Out of this world!!)
Great food but small--don't expect to hang out.
Great coffee, bagles, full breakfast menu, fantastic baked goods (made on site!), friendly service, and local appeal
Over priced!! $7 for bacon egg and cheese on a roll
Overpriced. Too cool for school server unable to make eye contact. You're in PSlope, not Wburg, smile.

The El Presidente, cheddar and jalapeño biscuit, peanut butter cookies,   Brooklyn Roasting Company coffee, and Divinitea loose teas are our favorite menu items. Add chorizo to the El Presidente for an explosion of flavors. Great service. Nice staff. One of our favorite weekend stops in Park Slope!

Owner is rude. Bought a cup of coffee and breakfast...sitting at table studying while eating, and when finished...she asked me to leave, informing me I can't study there. You own a coffee shop that people can't read in? Get real. If you have a shortage of tables, get more. You just lost a customer. Also, I'll be informing everyone I know of this ridiculousness. After reading other reviews, seems like you commonly ask people to vacate their tables.
Good coffee and food

Gorgeous sandwiches and the coffee is UNREAL. The staff are generally friendly as well. A little pricey for what it is but the unlimited amounts of vegetarian, gluten free, and special diet goodies make it a unique and safe place to bring anyone.

Just bought a yogurt dish, from this establishment.  Two spoons of yogurt , few strawberries and banana with dry granola at bottom for 6.25! to go! plastic container. A complete rip off!! Will never come back to this place again. Yes, the muffins look good and the burrito is fine, but this was disgraceful waste of money and showed a determined greed and felt like I was being cheated. Please pass this place by and go to many other worthwhile shops.

Cash only which is slightly annoying but then again almost all smaller restaurants are. Their breakfast burrito is good but nothing over-the -top. Pumpkin spiced latte around fall is good but definitely not worth the $5 or whatever that they charge.

The food isn't terrible. The service is that of a nasty farm animal sneering sideways at you constantly. The cashier needs to learn some manners. Her snide looks and demeanor are better suited as a nightclub Bouncer.  And, the audacity of the management/owner to send their patrons next door to restaurant next to them. My parents own a small diner in Queens and i know full well the costs of water used for toilets and sinks. Plus the additional costs of soaps, towels, electricity and cleaning. Not a good look!  Stay away at all costs!

Rude service. Period.  I have been a loyal patron of Naidre's for a year and had been thankful thus far that is seemed to be a place to enjoy time with friends and my baby who I come in with at least once a week. UNTIL TODAY.  I find it a true shame that I was asked to get up from my table today...where I sat with my baby while chatting with two other moms and their children, drinking coffee that I ordered from you...simply because I hadn't ordered anything from the kitchen. Aside from the fact that I order lunch and coffee there on a regular basis. It was inappropriate to ask me to get up and essentially leave and certainly did not go unnoticed by surrounding customers.  Anyone who runs a business with integrity, knows that it's about how you make your customers feel at the end of the day. That all of your patrons should be treated equally whether you are receiving $1 or $100 from them. I would expect a coffee shop as progressive as you claim to be to know that and operate under such a principle.  There are hundreds of coffee houses in Brooklyn....in Park Slope alone. I would think that in trying to survive this economy and thrive in your neighborhood, adopting a welcoming energy for every customer would be a great idea. Especially a customer with a baby in the Slope.
Naidre's is the kind of place you go to when you want to have some quiet time while getting work done.  No cell phones allowed!  I've had their salads quite a few time; simple and delicious.

Food is good but service is terrible. Not only they are slow but they have an attitude. The cashier (the white girl with the feathered hat, you know who she is) gave me such attitude because I asked her to give me a receipt. Shouldn't you get a receipt by law?
